GitHub - RegisJesuitRobotics/Competition2023: Robot code for FIRST Robotics...

Robot code for FIRST Robotics Competition 2023 CHARGED UP - GitHub - RegisJesuitRobotics/Competition2023: Robot code for FIRST Robotics Competition 2023 CHARGED UP

Awards

Our team won the Innovation in Control Award at Heartland Regional

Robot Overview

You can find details about our robot in the reveal thread

Code Features

  • Command-based Java
  • Log all the things (Custom telemetry classes that use NT and DataLog)
  • MK4i Falcon Swerve Chassis
  • Dual camera PhotonVision for pose estimation
  • Trapezoidal motion profiles on both arm and extension
  • Auto drive to node
    • Custom FWC plugin for node selection
  • LEDs:
    • Emulation of multiple LED strips but with only one PWM port
    • Priority based pattern picker

Programming Overview Judge Handout

The judge handout for this year can be found here

Logs

Should you be interested, 10GB of log files amassed throughout the season can be found in this repository:

GitHub

GitHub - RegisJesuitRobotics/Logs

Contribute to RegisJesuitRobotics/Logs development by creating an account on GitHub.

Future

During the offseason, we will be re-writing the code from scratch using AdvantageKit to explore the idea of using it in competition next year.

We are happy to answer any questions. Feedback is also appreciated.
